  "text": "Vasoconstriction not only lowers the PPG amplitude but also moves the dicrotic notch of the pulse wave proximally towards the systolic peak. 17 18 This was measured by the relative notch position (relative distance of the notch from the baseline of the pulse wave on the y-axis). The change of the relative notch position induced by tetanic stimulation was also similar in the groups and in responders and non-responders to tracheal intubation. Seitsonen and colleagues [CITATION_1] compared EEG, PPG and HR response induced by skin incision between subjects with and without motor response. The change in EEG response entropy, RR interval and PPG notch amplitude were parameters independently associated with motor response to the same stimulus (skin incision). Conversely our intention was to predict the response to a strong stimulus with the response to a weaker 'test stimulus', which turned out to be illusive.",
